[1] Guinea (Nzerekore): new case, situation update
Date: Wed 24 Feb 2021.
Source: Guinee Matin [in French, machine trans., edited]
https://guineematin.com/2021/02/24/ebola-un-nouveau-cas-positif-enregistre-a-gouecke/


Ebola: a new positive case recorded in Goueke

A new positive case of Ebola was recorded this Wednesday [24 Feb 2021], in the sub-prefecture of Goueke, prefecture of Nzerekore, where the disease reappeared recently. This brings to 5 the number of confirmed cases recorded since the resurgence of the epidemic in Guinea. The announcement was made by the National Health Security Agency (ANSS).

Guineematin.com offers you below the situation of the day communicated by the ANSS:
- Vaccination of 51 contacts around confirmed cases including 11 in Dubreka prefecture and 40 in Nzerekore on 23 Feb 2021;
- the result of the suspected case who died at the CT-Epi [epidemic treatment center] in Nzerekore on 23 Feb 2021 was negative;
- 1 new confirmed case among the contacts monitored was detected today [24 Feb 2021] in Goueke (Nzerekore);
- a cumulative total of 5 confirmed cases and 4 probable cases as of [23 Feb 2021];
- 2 confirmed cases are hospitalized at the CT-Epi in Nzerekore on 23 Feb 2021;
- no case hospitalized at the CT-Epi in Nongo (Conakry);
- 2 recoveries -- 1 in Conakry and 1 in Nzerekore;
- a cumulative total of 5 deaths including 4 probable cases and 1 confirmed case as of 23 Feb 2021;
- 106 contacts left the follow-up in Nzerekore as of 22 Feb 2021;
- to date, 276 contacts are being followed up.

--
