[2] Congo DR (North Kivu): 2 new cases
Date: Wed 24 Feb 2021
Source: Election-net [in French, machine trans., edited]
https://www.election-net.com/nord-kivu-ebola-deux-nouveaux-cas-positifs-enregistres-le-cumul-passe-a-8


According to the bulletin of the provincial technical commission at the Ministry of Health in North Kivu on Wednesday [24 Feb 2021], the province has notified 2 new positive cases of Ebola virus disease.

These new cases, which bring the total to 8, were recorded in the Biena Health Zone in Lubero territory.

It should be noted that since the resurgence of this epidemic in North Kivu, only 3 zones have been affected -- the Biena Health Zone, the Katwa Health Zone, and the Musienene Health Zone.

As a reminder, out of this total of 8 positive Ebola cases, 4 deaths were recorded -- 3 in Biena, and 1 in Katwa.

[Byline: Prince Bagheni]

--
Communicated by:
Mary Marshall
<mjm2020@googlemail.com>

[There is no additional information on these 2 new cases other than they were recorded in the Biena Health Zone in Lubero territory. It is not stated if they were known contacts of earlier cases, or whether they were among suspected cases. If not, it is of concern because if the virus is spreading beyond known contacts, there is a greater chance of losing control since the chain of transmission is not known. - Mod.LK]

